
@startuml

class Location {
  -address: string
  -drivers: List<Driver>
  -vehicles: List<Vehicle>
}

class Driver {
  -firstName: string
  -lastName: string
  -assignedOrder: Order (0..1)
  -assignedVehicle: Vehicle (0..1)
}

class Vehicle {
  -vehicleNumber: string
  -type: string
  -driver: Driver (0..1)
}

class Truck extends Vehicle {
  -weight: int
}

class Car extends Vehicle {
  -seats: int
}

class Van extends Vehicle {
  -capacity: int
}

class Order {
  -origin: Location
  -destination: Location
  -date: Date
  -drivers: List<Driver> (1..*)
}

Location "1" -- "0..*" Driver : has
Driver "1" -- "0..1" Order : carries
Driver "1" -- "0..1" Vehicle : drives
Vehicle "1" -- "0..1" Driver : driven by
Order "1" -- "1..*" Location : origin
Order "1" -- "1..*" Location : destination
Order "1" -- "1..*" Driver : assigned to
Truck --> Vehicle
Car --> Vehicle
Van --> Vehicle

@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- **Location** contains a list of **Drivers** and **Vehicles**.
- A **Driver** can be assigned to at most one **Order** and can drive at most one **Vehicle**.
- **Vehicles** are categorized into **Truck**, **Car**, and **Van**, each with specific attributes.
- An **Order** must have at least one **Driver** and is associated with an **Origin** and **Destination** location.
- Each **Vehicle** may be assigned to one **Driver**, and each **Driver** may be assigned to one **Vehicle**.

